  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6787.4 trading just above the 6780 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are positioned as stabilizers and likely buying this dip given the -1.2% 1-min move, while the massive +109.4B gamma wall at 6800 will trigger aggressive dealer selling pressure on any rally attempts. The thick positive gamma concentration between 6785-6800 creates a natural magnet effect, with dealers expected to fade moves in either direction within this range. Key levels: watch for dealer buying support around the 6780 flip and 6770 negative gamma pocket, while 6800 remains the critical resistance where dealer hedge selling intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward the 6785-6800 zone with limited breakout potential.",
